full_text: Dak Prescott: The official QB of #nflverse
I just got off the phone with #nflverse officials and they've assured me all non-Dak QBs have been removed from their various platforms
In our conversation, Ben Baldwin was particularly shocked to learn that Russell Wilson was still part of #nflverse. Said he would correct this immediately

jameis winston's interception numbers are misleading because he usually throws interceptions in low expected points situations anyways (i.e. 3rd and long, not in scoring position, etc.) #nflverse https://t.co/H0ocG20Yk9

That's correct. WOPR,RACR and some other variables have been added to the nflfastR player stats function. The weekly version can be loaded using nflreadr. Season summaries require the download of the pbp and running `calculate_player_stats` with the option `weekly=FALSE`#nflverse https://t.co/jrQt0mBz0m https://t.co/zWhG600qOu

Currently revisiting SIS passing accuracy data which includes On Target Percentage Above Average (OTAA) split by area of the field. And whelp Carson Wentz in 2020 was....different. 
#nflverse https://t.co/2ag2nYZ9u1
How does an insanely good OTAA plot look like? #nflverse https://t.co/U5lfH1NFpY

Alright @nfl_data_py 0.2.4 is up and running with a function for caching pbp data locally -> cache_pbp(); and an updated load_pbp_data() function for pulling data directly from that cache. Check it out and let me know if you have any trouble: https://t.co/jCRM1hlZPa #nflverse

@CowboysStats Only one QB has been more vindicated  by the #nflverse than Dak Prescott.

That QB would be Antonio Ramiro (Tony) Romo.
@CowboysStats @CowboysStats, please stop abusing the #nflverse hashtag
Warren Sharp is a no talent hack #nflverse

Using @nflseedR or any other packages in the #nflverse family?

Use the hashtag to get a retweet from this bot, and follow the bot to see others' work! https://t.co/DzRzPbkCdN
DESPITE BEING 19% #nflverse https://t.co/biFVq732WE

Hey! I am a bot that retweets the #nflverse hashtag. 
üèà----------------üñ•Ô∏è

So if you are doing football analysis and would like me to help you spread your findings, just use the above hashtag.

Inspired by the now famous @tejfbanalytics interception risk chart, I decided to extend the plot to also include fumbles.

Baker, Jameis and Allen seem to take calculated risks. Burrow on the other hand...

#nflverse https://t.co/f5gksUcgXP

We're 9 days from the start of the NFL regular season and trade activity is starting to pick up. Here is how many trades there have been in the 14 days leading up to the regular season in past years.

Data: #nflverse https://t.co/nG48tTXDWD

#FlyEaglesFly add Gardner Minshew for a conditional 6th Round Pick. Gardner is a young low-cost below average starter who might see the field if Jalen Hurts struggles early in the season. #nflverse https://t.co/cjRjIb9kZk

Winston is a good player, but his streak of int rate is worrying.

Better Winston than Hill, of course
 #nflverse https://t.co/IWHuS4Z2jo

Today i see 27 dropbacks of Josh Allen on 33 plays. 
I think, we will see another heavy pass year in Buffalo this year. #nflverse https://t.co/5Ei8uzmWDD
*pokes the new #nflverse retweet bot* https://t.co/M4f3gBn5w0

Tonight on-stream: as yet undecided! Probably will work on setting up data and infrastructure for simulating individual in-season weeks in ffsimulator. Might be a shiny app night. Whatever it is, it'll be #rstats and #nflverse!

Live at about 8pm EDT: https://t.co/byE0SlXj3e
